%sql
CREATE TEMPORARY VIEW amzn_reviews_cnt AS (
   SELECT product_id, 
          COUNT(*) AS cnt,
          SUM(helpful_votes) AS helpful_votes_cnt,
          SUM(total_votes) AS total_votes_cnt,
          SUM(CASE WHEN verified_purchase = 'Y' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS verified_purchase_cnt,
          SUM(CASE WHEN vine = 'Y' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS vine_cnt
   FROM amzn_reviews
   GROUP BY product_id)

paragraphs.text:
%sql
CREATE TEMPORARY VIEW amzn_reviews_mean AS (
   SELECT product_id, 
          MEAN(star_rating) AS star_rating_mean,
          MEAN(helpful_votes) AS helpful_votes_mean,
          MEAN(total_votes) AS total_votes_mean,
          MEAN(CASE WHEN verified_purchase = 'Y' THEN star_rating ELSE NULL END) AS star_rating_with_verified_purchase_mean,
          MEAN(CASE WHEN vine = 'Y' THEN star_rating ELSE NULL END) AS star_rating_with_vine_mean,
          MEAN(star_rating * (helpful_votes + 1)) AS star_rating_with_votes_mean,
          MEAN(star_rating * (helpful_votes + 1) / (total_votes + 1)) AS star_rating_helpful_votes_weighted_mean
   FROM amzn_reviews
   GROUP BY product_id)

%sql
CREATE TEMPORARY VIEW amzn_reviews_agg AS (
    SELECT amzn_item_lookup.product_id as product_id, 
    *,
    helpful_votes_cnt / total_votes_cnt as helpful_votes_ratio,
    verified_purchase_cnt / cnt as verified_purchase_ratio,
    vine_cnt / cnt as vine_ratio
    FROM amzn_item_lookup
    INNER JOIN
    amzn_reviews_cnt
    ON amzn_item_lookup.product_id = amzn_reviews_cnt.product_id
    INNER JOIN
    amzn_reviews_mean
    ON amzn_reviews_cnt.product_id = amzn_reviews_mean.product_id
    INNER JOIN
    amzn_reviews_scores_agg
    ON amzn_reviews_mean.product_id = amzn_reviews_scores_agg.product_id)

%pyspark
# Getting rid of duplicate columns
from collections import Counter

column_names = sqlContext.sql('SHOW COLUMNS IN amzn_reviews_ds_with_dups')
column_names = column_names.toPandas()['col_name']
column_names_counter = Counter()
new_column_names = []
for col_name in column_names:
    column_names_counter[col_name] += 1
    new_column_names.append(col_name if column_names_counter[col_name] == 1 else str(col_name) + '_' + 
        str(column_names_counter[col_name]) + '_DUP')
        
df = sqlContext.table("amzn_reviews_ds_with_dups").toDF(*new_column_names)

# Get rid of duplicate rows with Pandas
p_df = df.toPandas()
p_df.drop_duplicates(subset=['product_title', 'product_category'], keep=False, inplace=True)
p_df = p_df[[col for col in p_df.columns if not col.endswith('_DUP')]]
df = sqlContext.createDataFrame(p_df)

df.createOrReplaceTempView("amzn_reviews_ds")

%pyspark
from pyspark.sql.functions import *
from pyspark.ml.feature import StandardScaler
from pyspark.ml.feature import VectorAssembler
from pyspark.ml.feature import StringIndexer, OneHotEncoder
from pyspark.sql.types import DoubleType
from pyspark.ml.regression import LinearRegression
from pyspark.ml.regression import GBTRegressor

from pyspark.ml import Pipeline

dataFrame = sqlContext.table("amzn_reviews_ds")
dataFrame = dataFrame.withColumn("label", dataFrame["percent_rank"])
dataFrame = dataFrame.filter("cnt > 20")
# dataFrame = dataFrame.withColumn("star_rating_with_verified_purchase_weighted_mean", expr("IF(star_rating_with_verified_purchase_mean IS NULL OR isNaN(star_rating_with_verified_purchase_mean),  star_rating_mean, (star_rating_with_verified_purchase_mean + star_rating_mean) / 2)"))

cat_string_indexer = StringIndexer(inputCol="product_category", outputCol="product_category_idx")
cat_ohe = OneHotEncoder(inputCol="product_category_idx", outputCol="product_category_vec")
# dataFrame = ohe.transform(dataFrame)

(training, test) = dataFrame.randomSplit([.7, .3], seed=42)

assembler = VectorAssembler(
    inputCols=['product_category_vec', 'star_rating_mean', 'cnt', 'total_votes_mean', 'helpful_votes_mean', 'sentiment_score_mean'],
    outputCol="unscaled_features")
    
# output = assembler.transform(training)
    
scaler = StandardScaler(
                        inputCol="unscaled_features", outputCol="features",
                        withStd=True, withMean=False)

# lr = LinearRegression(maxIter=10, regParam=.01)
clf = GBTRegressor(featuresCol="features", maxIter=10)


stages = [cat_string_indexer, cat_ohe, assembler, scaler, clf]
pipeline = Pipeline(stages=stages)

model = pipeline.fit(training)
prediction = model.transform(training)
prediction.show()

# # Compute summary statistics by fitting the StandardScaler
# scalerModel = scaler.fit(output)

# # Normalize each feature to have unit standard deviation.
# dataFrame = scalerModel.transform(output)
# dataFrame.show()

%pyspark
from pyspark.ml.evaluation import RegressionEvaluator
eval = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol="label", predictionCol="prediction", metricName="rmse")

# Root Mean Square Error
rmse = eval.evaluate(prediction)
print("RMSE: %.3f" % rmse)

# Mean Square Error
mse = eval.evaluate(prediction, {eval.metricName: "mse"})
print("MSE: %.3f" % mse)

# Mean Absolute Error
mae = eval.evaluate(prediction, {eval.metricName: "mae"})
print("MAE: %.3f" % mae)

# r2 - coefficient of determination
r2 = eval.evaluate(prediction, {eval.metricName: "r2"})
print("r2: %.3f" %r2)

%pyspark
